# Bolt.new MVP Prompt - Nyumba Connect Housing Rental Platform

## Primary Instruction

Create a **Minimum Viable Product (MVP)** for "Nyumba Connect" - a simple but functional housing rental platform for Tanzania. Focus on core features that solve the main problem: connecting property owners with tenants quickly and efficiently.

## MVP Core Features (Essential Only)

### 1. Simple User System
- **Basic registration**: Name, email, phone, user type (Tenant/Landlord)
- **Simple login**: Email and password only
- **Basic profile**: Avatar, contact info, verification badge (mock)
- **No complex verification process** - keep it simple

### 2. Property Listing (Landlords)
- **Add Property Form** with essential fields only:
  - Property title
  - Description (textarea)
  - Property type (dropdown: House, Apartment, Room)
  - Bedrooms and bathrooms (number inputs)
  - Monthly rent price
  - Location (city and area - text inputs)
  - Contact phone number
  - Upload 3-5 photos
- **My Properties page**: Simple list of landlord's properties
- **Edit/Delete property** basic functionality

### 3. Property Search (Tenants)
- **Homepage with search bar**: Search by city/area
- **Simple filters**: 
  - Price range (min-max slider)
  - Property type
  - Number of bedrooms
- **Property listings page**: Grid of property cards
- **Property details page**: 
  - Photo gallery (simple carousel)
  - Property info and description
  - Landlord contact info
  - "Contact Owner" button (opens WhatsApp/call)

### 4. Basic Contact System
- **Direct contact**: Click button opens WhatsApp with pre-filled message
- **Phone call option**: Click to call landlord
- **Simple contact form**: Send message to landlord (stores in simple list)

### 5. Essential Pages Only
- **Homepage**: Hero section, search bar, featured properties (6-8 properties)
- **Property Listings**: Search results with basic filters
- **Property Details**: Full property information
- **Add Property**: Simple form for landlords
- **My Properties**: Landlord's property dashboard
- **Login/Register**: Basic authentication pages
- **Profile**: Basic user profile page

## Technical Requirements (Simplified)

### Tech Stack
- **React.js** with functional components
- **Tailwind CSS** for styling
- **React Router** for navigation
- **Local Storage** for data persistence
- **JSON data structure** for properties and users
- **No real backend** - just local storage simulation

### Data Structure (Simple JSON)
```javascript
// Users
{
  id: "uuid",
  name: "John Doe",
  email: "john@email.com",
  phone: "0712345678",
  userType: "landlord", // or "tenant"
  avatar: "url",
  createdAt: "date"
}

// Properties
{
  id: "uuid",
  ownerId: "user-uuid",
  title: "3 Bedroom House in Kinondoni",
  description: "Beautiful house with garden...",
  type: "house", // house, apartment, room
  bedrooms: 3,
  bathrooms: 2,
  price: 800000, // monthly rent in TZS
  city: "Dar es Salaam",
  area: "Kinondoni",
  phone: "0712345678",
  images: ["url1", "url2", "url3"],
  createdAt: "date",
  isAvailable: true
}
```

## Sample Data to Include

### Properties (12-15 sample properties)
1. **Dar es Salaam properties** (6-7):
   - 2BR apartment in Mikocheni - 600,000 TZS
   - 3BR house in Kinondoni - 800,000 TZS  
   - 1BR room in Ubungo - 250,000 TZS
   - 4BR house in Msasani - 1,200,000 TZS
   - Studio apartment in Upanga - 350,000 TZS
   - 2BR apartment in Temeke - 450,000 TZS

2. **Other cities** (6-8):
   - 3BR house in Arusha - 700,000 TZS
   - 2BR apartment in Mwanza - 500,000 TZS
   - 1BR room in Dodoma - 200,000 TZS
   - 2BR house in Mbeya - 400,000 TZS

### Sample Users
- **3-4 landlords** with multiple properties each
- **2-3 tenants** for testing
- Realistic Tanzanian names and phone numbers

## UI/UX Requirements (Simple & Clean)

### Design Guidelines
- **Clean, minimal design** - no fancy animations
- **Mobile-first** responsive design
- **Simple color scheme**: 
  - Primary: Blue (#3B82F6)
  - Secondary: Green (#10B981)  
  - Background: White/Gray
- **Easy navigation** with clear menu
- **Large, clickable buttons** for mobile users
- **Simple forms** with clear labels

### Key Components
1. **Property Card**: Image, title, price, location, bedrooms
2. **Search Bar**: Location input with search button
3. **Filter Panel**: Simple checkboxes and sliders
4. **Contact Buttons**: WhatsApp and Call buttons
5. **Image Gallery**: Simple photo carousel
6. **Form Components**: Input fields, dropdowns, file upload

## Specific Pages (MVP Only)

### 1. Homepage (`/`)
- Hero section with search bar
- "Nyumba Connect - Pata Nyumba Rahisi"
- Featured properties section (8 properties)
- Simple footer with contact info

### 2. Property Listings (`/properties`)
- Search results grid
- Simple sidebar with filters
- "Load More" button (instead of pagination)

### 3. Property Details (`/property/:id`)
- Image gallery at top
- Property information
- Landlord contact section
- WhatsApp and Call buttons

### 4. Add Property (`/add-property`)
- Simple form with all required fields
- Image upload (drag & drop or file picker)
- Save to local storage

### 5. My Properties (`/my-properties`)
- List of landlord's properties
- Edit/Delete buttons
- Add new property button

### 6. Login (`/login`) & Register (`/register`)
- Simple forms
- Role selection (Tenant/Landlord)
- Store in local storage

### 7. Profile (`/profile`)
- Basic user info
- Edit profile option
- Logout button

## Essential Functionality

### Search & Filter
- **Text search**: Match property title, description, location
- **Price filter**: Min-max range slider
- **Property type filter**: Checkboxes
- **Bedroom filter**: Dropdown (1, 2, 3, 4+ bedrooms)

### Contact System
- **WhatsApp integration**: Pre-filled message "Hi, I'm interested in your property: [Property Title]"
- **Phone calls**: Direct dial from mobile browsers
- **Simple inquiry form**: Name, phone, message (save to local storage)

### Image Handling
- **Upload multiple images**: File input with preview
- **Image carousel**: Simple prev/next navigation
- **Responsive images**: Proper sizing for mobile/desktop

## User Flow (Simplified)

### For Tenants:
1. Visit homepage → Search by location
2. Browse results → Apply simple filters
3. Click property → View details
4. Contact landlord → WhatsApp/Call directly

### For Landlords:
1. Register as landlord → Login
2. Add property → Fill simple form + upload photos
3. Manage properties → View inquiries
4. Receive contacts via WhatsApp/phone

## What NOT to Include (Keep it Simple)

❌ **No booking system** - just direct contact  
❌ **No payment integration** - landlords handle payments directly  
❌ **No messaging system** - use WhatsApp instead  
❌ **No reviews/ratings** - keep it simple  
❌ **No maps integration** - just text location  
❌ **No advanced search** - basic filters only  
❌ **No user verification** - trust-based system  
❌ **No admin panel** - not needed for MVP  
❌ **No email notifications** - rely on direct contact  

## Success Criteria for MVP

✅ **Users can register and login**  
✅ **Landlords can add properties with photos**  
✅ **Tenants can search and find properties**  
✅ **Contact system works (WhatsApp/phone)**  
✅ **Responsive design works on mobile**  
✅ **Data persists in browser storage**  
✅ **All core pages load without errors**  

## Development Notes

### Keep It Simple
- Use placeholder images for properties
- Focus on functionality over fancy design
- Make forms easy to fill on mobile
- Ensure fast loading times
- Test on mobile devices first

### Future Enhancements (After MVP)
- Add real backend (Supabase)
- Implement booking system
- Add payment integration
- Include maps and location features
- Add messaging system
- Implement user verification

## Final Instructions

Create a **working, functional MVP** that solves the core problem: helping people find and list rental properties in Tanzania. Keep it simple, clean, and focused on essential features only. The goal is to validate the idea quickly and get user feedback before building complex features.

Make sure the app works well on mobile phones since most users in Tanzania primarily use mobile devices. Focus on speed, simplicity, and ease of use.